<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 6:51AM EDT  by NWS Pittsburgh</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT NORTHEASTERN HARRISON...CENTRAL
JEFFERSON AND SOUTHEASTERN CARROLL COUNTIES THROUGH 715 AM EDT...
At 651 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Cadiz, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Steubenville, Cadiz, Wintersville, Mingo Junction, Hopedale,
Smithfield, Scio, Jewett, Amsterdam, Richmond, New Alexandria, and
Bloomingdale.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
